Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} (spread out across entire sheet for 4). Toss potatoes on empty side of baking sheet with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} (use a separate #baking sheet{} for 4). Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. (For 4, roast potatoes on top rack and carrots on middle rack.)

Once veggies have roasted 10 minutes, pat chicken dry with #paper towels{}; place between two large pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until chicken is about 1⁄2 inch thick. Season all over with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @bavette steak{10%ounce}; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. TIP: Lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

Transfer steak to a #cutting board{}.

> Swap in steak for chicken. Cook steak to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

In a large #bowl{}, combine @arugula{2%ounce}, roasted carrots, and @blue cheese dressing{1.5%ounce}.

Slice steak crosswise.

> Slice steak against the grain.

Divide arugula and blue cheese salad and potato wedges between plates in separate sections. Top salad with steak and garnish with @walnuts{0.5%ounce}. Serve.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.